      <description>Carl T. Ford Jr. was born in Baton Rouge, La., on June 17, 1923, to Carl
            T. Ford Sr. and Julia Collins Ford. He graduated from McKinley High School in Baton
            Rouge in 1943 and served in the U.S. Army during World War II. He was a coach at
            McKinley High School between 1960 and 1983.</description>
